    "In this phase, the methodology proposed in Phase 1 is implemented on the selected student mental health dataset. The dataset was cleaned, preprocessed, and feature-engineered in earlier phases. In this phase, multiple machine learning models are trained and tested to predict student depression level. Since the target variable contains multiple classes, model performance is evaluated using multiclass classification metrics such as accuracy, weighted precision, weighted recall, weighted F1-score, and ROC-AUC. The models are then compared to identify the best-performing approach, and feature importance analysis is used to determine the most influential predictors. The overall goal is to assess predictive performance and identify meaningful factors associated with student depression."
